Read the implementation spec at `.hanness/pages/page_02_combination_engine.page` and implement everything described.

Prerequisites: page_01 must be complete (CardDefs.js and CardStack.js exist).

Steps:
1. Create `client/src/logic/CombinationEngine.js`.
2. Define the RECIPES array with all recipes from the spec (natural gather, threat combat, resource, weapon, population, construction, PvP dispatch).
3. Implement CombinationEngine class with findRecipe(), combine(), calcKingdomScore(), _calcPopLimit(), _calcFarmLimit() methods.
4. Ensure bidirectional recipe matching (A+B and B+A both work).
5. Ensure populationCheck and farmlandCheck logic is correct per CLAUDE.md §5.3, §5.4.

After implementing, verify each acceptance criterion listed at the bottom of the spec.
